            </div>
            <p class="name" data-uuid="ced56d3f1ca04141b1843ec1676f85e8">Benjamin
                Banneker</p>
            <p class="date" data-uuid="582c150bcdf748c682f6f3cd16d77f97">(1731–1806)</p>
            <figure class="bio-image" data-uuid="9c57c4db3e764b8997a8e2fa4e718ea4">
                <img alt="This is an artist's rendering of Benjamin Banneker." src="../../img/module_7_lesson02/ms_snlese454149_841p.png" data-uuid="6b126d4524554366a9e863153dd2965f" />
            </figure>
            <p data-uuid="48a0c872050c452984a9936b5a1020ff">Benjamin Banneker was born to
                a free African American family in rural Maryland. He attended a Quaker school
                but was largely self-educated. He was a skilled mathematician and scientist. His
                mathematical skills prompted Thomas Jefferson to give him a job surveying the
                land for the new national capital.&#160;</p>
